article.headline: Northern Arizona 61, Montana 55
article.story:
MISSOULA (AP) -- Megan Rice had 17 points and six rebounds
Saturday as Northern Arizona ended Montana's 23-game Big Sky
Conference winning streak with a 61-55 loss.

Northern Arizona (16-8, 7-4) controlled the game and Montana
(16-7, 9-1) was unable to lead by more than two points.

The game was tied for the ninth time, at 48-all on a basket by
Montana's Dana Conway with 5:45 remaining.

A three-point play by Nicky Eason and a 3-pointer by Teresa Diaz
gave the Lumberjacks a 54-48 lead with 4:26 to play.

NAU took a 56-49 lead on a layup by Rice, but back-to-back
baskets by Lynsey Monaco and Hollie Tyler got Montana within 56-53
with 1:47 remaining.

The teams traded layups, Montana was forced to foul and NAU made
3-of-4 free throws in the final 14 seconds.

Wakefield and Eason each finished with 12 points for NAU, which
led by as many as nine points in the first half. Alyssa Wahl added
10 points for Northern Arizona.

Tyler led UM with 14 points and five blocked shots while Jody
McLeod had 11 points and 10 rebounds. The Lady Griz missed all
eight of their 3-point attempts.
